Diagnosis
. MALE. Clypeus deeply concave, shiny, with sculptured narrow anterior border (
Fig. 6D
); scape not widened apically; F1 strongly compressed, wider than F2. Pronotum with sparse subappressed and erect pale setae; propodeum dorsally with sparse pale setae and visible sculpture (
Fig. 3D
). Metacoxa beneath totally flattened and closed with very short dense pubescence (
Fig. 7G
). Hypopygium (S8) with short longitudinal lateral ridge reaching posterior 1/2 of sternum; cuspis lamellate, reaching posterior 1/2 of paramere. FEMALE. T2 pale setal spots small, distance between them 1.0 × or more than spot diameter (
Fig. 4C
); T3–4 with a pair of small lateral pale setal spots, distance between spots and that between spot and lateral margin of tergum approximately equal to spot diameter (
Fig. 4C
); pygidial plate with weak transversal curved rugae laterally oriented to apex (
Fig. 12G
).
